div.div: High-school beauty Umaru seems like the perfect teen wunderkind, but she's hiding a shocking double life. As soon as she gets home, she becomes a junk-food-inhaling, soda-guzzling, video-game-addicted slob. The only one who sees this unsavory side of Umaru is her beleaguered older brother Taihei, who does his best to keep up with his work while trying to get his little sister to behave like a decent member of society. As she makes new friends and gets into a number of wacky situations, Umaru will continue to fight for her right to stay up all night binging potato chips and anime. (Source: Anime News Network)
Episodes included in the manga's seventh and tenth volume.
Ore dake Level Up na Ken: Season 2 - Arise from the Shadow
The second season of Solo Leveling. Mastering his new abilities in secret, Jin-U must battle humanity's toughest foes to save his mother. (Source: Crunchyroll News)
Otonari no Tenshi-sama ni Itsunomanika Dame Ningen ni Sareteita Ken

Amane Fujimiya lives alone in a messy apartment—right next door to Mahiru Shiina, a veritable "angel" who's the smartest, prettiest girl at school. When a chance encounter on a rainy day draws them together, Mahiru finds herself spending more and more time helping Amane get his life in order. And though they both insist they have no intention of dating the other, slowly but surely, something more than friendship begins to blossom.
(Source: Square Enix)

Jihan Han is your typical high school student -- minus the fact the he’s acquired the special ability to view the world around him as a video-game. Not long after this discovery, he stumbles upon a hidden world filled with others just like him. Now, amidst juggling homework and completing quests, Jihan must learn how to navigate his newfound power in order to level up in life.
(Source: WEBTOONS)

Ga-Jang No is a strong, dedicated, and humble man, with much respect for the martial arts. After the death of his lovely wife, this muscle-for-hire just wants an easy job that allows him to be a good father to his three little babies. He’s even happy to pull guard duty and fend off amateur fighters if it means he can return home safely each night. But when a creepy cult starts stealing children from the city, Ga-Jang must step up to the challenge and discover his true warrior potential.
(Source: Tapas, edited)

My name is Yu Il-Sin, a third-rate web novel author. I discovered a strange gaming app and was judged to be a G-rank hunter. You save the world in the game and gain divine powers you can use in real life. It's a little bit strange, somehow? My follower count and the number of quests keep increasing. In the midst of this, when should I write my web novel? It's suspended for personal reasons... No, I'm starting the serialization. (Source: Naver, translated) Note: Chapter count includes a prologue.
Comedy, Ecchi, Romance, Slice of Life

Sakurai Shinichi’s one wish is for a little peace and quiet. But Uzaki Hana–his boisterous, well-endowed underclassman–has other plans. All she wants is to hang out and poke fun at him. With the help of her chipper charm and peppy persistence, this might just be the start of a beautiful relationship!
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)
